<plot>Little Audrey, forced to stay indoors because of the rain, wishes that it would never rain again. Her wish comes true and the Mississippy River dries up and Niagara Falls disappears. Speakeasies come back, where men with money can get an eyedropper of water, while the flowers, trees and grass die for lack of water. Little Audrey is sorry and a little drop of rainwater takes her to the rainmaker to see if she can make him relent. Little Audrey's sad story makes him cry, and his tears spill over the clouds as rainwater.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?051020</url></doc>
